description:
&lt;p&gt;Salisbury Hospice at Home service has been providing care for people at the end of their lives in the home environment for 4 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people who are familiar with the Hospice at Home service and who can provide personal care, emotional support and know how to care for the dying in the home environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a small team who are dedicated to providing the best possible care. When people are dying there is only one chance to get it right and so we need people with the right skills and attitudes. You will need great communication skills and the ability to work autonomously in the home supported by a co-ordinator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a short term contract until 31 March 2021 with a view to extending it from April 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mandy Coombes Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;mandy.coombes1@nhs.net 01722 425113&lt;/p&gt;
